Dry spells are expected over parts of Botswana as a result of tropical Cyclone Enawo. ALSO READ: Cyclone Enawo on its way This is according to Botswana&#8217;s meteorological services department on Tuesday, who said the cyclone would drive away moisture, an ingredient for rainfall formation, SAnews.gov.za-NNN-PANA reports. Cyclone Enawo was expected to hit Madagascar on Tuesday in the form of a tropical depression, with a lot of rainfall and possible flooding. The Botswana department reportedly did, however, expect thundershowers in the extreme northern parts of the country on Wednesday. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.